==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hookah
<hw>Hook"ah</hw> <pr>(h⟦oocr⟧k"⟦adot⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Per. or
Ar. <ets>huqqa</ets> a round box or casket, a bottle through which the
fumes pass when smoking tobacco.]</ety> <def>A pipe with a long,
flexible stem, so arranged that the smoke is cooled by being made to
pass through water. Also called <altname>narghile</altname> and
<altname>water pipe</altname>. The <er>hubble-bubble</er> is a simple
form of this device.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>hook-and-ladder company</ent>⟦br⟧
